Sentencas: A redox-stable and catalytically active electrode (PrBa)(0.95)(Fe0.9Mo0.1)(2)O5+delta (PBFM) is synthesized and evaluated as both air electrode and hydrogen electrode for symmetrical solid oxide steam electrolysis cells (SOECs).
Titulo: Layered perovskite (PrBa)0.95(Fe0.9Mo0.1)2O5+δ as electrode materials for high-performing symmetrical solid oxide electrolysis cells

Sentencas: The XRD analysis presents that the PBFM has a layered perovskite structure.
Titulo: Layered perovskite (PrBa)0.95(Fe0.9Mo0.1)2O5+δ as electrode materials for high-performing symmetrical solid oxide electrolysis cells

Sentencas: The symmetric electrolysis cell with configuration of PBFM/La0.8Sr0.2Ga0.87Mg0.13O3 (LSGM)/PBFM exhibits a relatively high electrolysis current density of 510 mA cm(2) at 800 degrees C when the applied voltage is set at 1.3 V.
Titulo: Layered perovskite (PrBa)0.95(Fe0.9Mo0.1)2O5+δ as electrode materials for high-performing symmetrical solid oxide electrolysis cells

Sentencas: In addition, the durability of the cell at a constant electrolysis voltage of 1.3 V is also tested and there is no obvious degradation found during the process.
Titulo: Layered perovskite (PrBa)0.95(Fe0.9Mo0.1)2O5+δ as electrode materials for high-performing symmetrical solid oxide electrolysis cells
